LICENSE-THIRD-PARTY
===================

This project source code is licensed under MIT (see LICENSE).
Third-party dependencies and runtime model backends are governed by their own
licenses and terms.

Core/runtime dependencies (representative)
-----------------------------------------
- librosa: ISC
- scikit-learn: BSD-3-Clause
- numpy: BSD-3-Clause
- scipy: BSD-3-Clause
- soundfile: BSD-3-Clause
- torch: BSD-3-Clause
- transformers: Apache-2.0
- openai-whisper: MIT
- stable-ts: MIT

Runtime model backends
----------------------
- handcrafted (`handcrafted`): librosa feature stack (ISC/BSD dependencies)
- XLS-R (`hf_xlsr`): Apache-2.0 model family
  Source: https://huggingface.co/facebook/wav2vec2-xls-r-300m
- Whisper (`hf_whisper`): MIT model family
  Source: https://github.com/openai/whisper/blob/main/LICENSE
- emotion2vec (`emotion2vec`): custom model license (`other`)
  Source: https://github.com/modelscope/FunASR/blob/main/MODEL_LICENSE
  Status: restricted, explicit opt-in required via
  `SER_ENABLE_RESTRICTED_BACKENDS=true`.

Notes
-----
- This project does not bundle third-party model weights in package artifacts.
- Training data licenses can impose additional constraints on derived artifacts.
- See runtime policy helpers in `ser/license_check.py` for enforced backend
  license gates and provenance fields.
